<Feedforward Candidate Generator Summary: filter>
- Purpose: generate two filtering-focused feedforward candidates from InputData.
- Output format: valid JSON object only, no extra text.

Core expectations:
- Prioritize spatialContextTypes and embodiment context for filter reasoning.
- If deictic speech appears and gaze target exists, anchor filters around gaze-near datapoints.
- Propose new filtering actions, not restatements of current chart state.
- Populate c1 and c2 using cluster fields from InputData without schema changes.
- Fill filter-related fields (x, y, z, type) consistently with candidate insight.

Filtering guidance:
- Support RangeAdjustment or AttributeFilter.
- Use concrete values from row_values and keep effect as a separate sentence.
- Prefer unexplored ranges or attributes over repeated conditions.

Public-release note:
- Detailed policy rules and long examples are omitted in this public release.
</Feedforward Candidate Generator Summary: filter>
